ito in 2016.jpg|150px|right|thumbnail|[[Tomatito]]]]\n* [[Teye]] (Teije Wijnterp)\n* [[Tomatito]] (Jos\u00e9 Fern\u00e1ndez Torres)\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of classical guitarists]]\n\n{{Portal bar|Lists}}\n\n==References==\n\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{wikimedia|Flamenco guitarists|collapsible=true|c=Category:Flamenco guitar|}}\n\n{{Flamenco guitar}}\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Flamenco guitarists}}\n[[Category:Flamenco guitarists| ]]\n[[Category:Lists of guitarists]]\n", "name_user": "AMM Pittsburgh", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eA:added *Aniya la Gitana", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_flamenco_guitarists"}
{"title_page": "Markus M\u00fcller", "text_new": "{{for|the Swiss Olympic gymnast|Markus M\u00fcller (gymnast)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2011}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name                = Markus M\u00fcller\n| image               = \n| caption             = \n| fullname            = \n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1988|5|22}}\n| birth_place         = [[Eberswalde]], [[East Germany]]\n| height              = {{Height|m=1.89}}\n| position            = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| currentclub         = [[Teutonia Watzenborn-Steinberg]]\n| clubnumber          = 10\n| youthyears1         = 1996\u20132000\n| youthclubs1         = ESV Zschorlau\n| youthyears2         = 2000\u20132007\n| youthclubs2         = [[Erzgebirge Aue]]\n| years1              = 2007\u20132009\n| clubs1              = [[Erzgebirge Aue]]\n| caps1               = 5\n| goals1              = 0\n| years2              = 2009\u20132011\n| clubs2              = [[Hallescher FC]]\n| caps2               = 54\n| goals2              = 9\n| years3              = 2011\u20132013\n| clubs3              = [[SV Babelsberg 03]]\n| caps3               = 67\n| goals3              = 16\n| years4              = 2013\u20132014\n| clubs4              = [[Wormatia Worms]]\n| caps4               = 9\n| goals4              = 2\n| years5              = 2014\u20132016\n| clubs5              = [[Kickers Offenbach]]\n| caps5               = 81\n| goals5              = 30\n| years6              = 2016\u2013\n| clubs6              = [[Teutonia Watzenborn-Steinberg]]\n| caps6               = 0\n| goals6              = 0\n| totalcaps           = \n| totalgoals          = \n| nationalyears1      = \n| nationalteam1       = \n| nationalcaps1       = \n| nationalgoals1      = \n| medaltemplates      = \n| club-update         = 23 July 2016\n| nationalteam-update = \n}}\n'''Markus M\u00fcller''' (born 22 May 1988) is a German [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Teutonia Watzenborn-Steinberg]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/regionalliga/rlsw/regionalliga-suedwest-2012/2016-17/teutonia-watzenborn-steinberg-7607/48626/spieler_markus-mueller.html | title = M\u00fcller, Markus | language = German | publisher = kicker.de | accessdate = 10 August 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\nM\u00fcller began his career with [[Erzgebirge Aue]], and made his debut in the [[2. Bundesliga]] in April 2008, replacing [[Florian Heller]] in a 0\u20130 home draw with [[1. FC Kaiserslautern]]. He left Aue in January 2009 to join [[Hallescher FC]] of the [[Regionalliga Nord]], where he spent two and a half seasons, being released in June 2011 after injury had restricted him to just eight appearances in the previous season. He subsequently joined [[SV Babelsberg 03]] of the [[3. Liga]], for whom he scored 12 goals in the [[2011\u201312 3. Liga|2011\u201312 season]]. After Babelsberg were relegated in the 2012\u201313 season, he left to sign for [[Wormatia Worms]], where he spent six months before joining [[Kickers Offenbach]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{fussballdaten|muellermarkus|Markus M\u00fcller}}\n* {{soccerway}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Muller, Markus}}\n[[Category:1988 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:German footballers]]\n[[Category:FC Erzgebirge Aue players]]\n[[Category:Hallescher FC players]]\n[[Category:SV Babelsberg 03 players]]\n[[Category:Wormatia Worms players]]\n[[Category:Kickers Offenbach players]]\n[[Category:2. Bundesliga players]]\n[[Category:3. Liga players]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n\n\n{{Germany-footy-forward-1980s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{for|the Swiss Olympic gymnast|Markus M\u00fcller (gymnast)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2011}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name                = Markus M\u00fcller\n| image               = \n| caption             = \n| fullname            = \n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1988|5|22}}\n| birth_place         = [[Eberswalde]], [[East Germany]]\n| height              = {{Height|m=1.89}}\n| position            = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| currentclub         = [[Teutonia Watzenborn-Steinberg]]\n| clubnumber          = 10\n| youthyears1         = 1996\u20132000\n| youthclubs1         = ESV Zschorlau\n| youthyears2         = 2000\u20132007\n| youthclubs2         = [[Erzgebirge Aue]]\n| years1              = 2007\u20132009\n| clubs1              = [[Erzgebirge Aue]]\n| caps1               = 5\n| goals1              = 0\n| years2              = 2009\u20132011\n| clubs2              = [[Hallescher FC]]\n| caps2               = 54\n| goals2              = 9\n| years3              = 2011\u20132013\n| clubs3              = [[SV Babelsberg 03]]\n| caps3               = 67\n| goals3              = 16\n| years4              = 2013\u20132014\n| clubs4              = [[Wormatia Worms]]\n| caps4               = 9\n| goals4              = 2\n| years5              = 2014\u20132016\n| clubs5              = [[Kickers Offenbach]]\n| caps5               = 81\n| goals5              = 30\n| years6              = 2016\u2013\n| clubs6              = [[Teutonia Watzenborn-Steinberg]]\n| caps6               = 0\n| goals6              = 0\n| totalcaps           = \n| totalgoals          = \n| nationalyears1      = \n| nationalteam1       = \n| nationalcaps1       = \n| nationalgoals1      = \n| medaltemplates      = \n| club-update         = 23 July 2016\n| nationalteam-update = \n}}\n'''Markus M\u00fcller''' (born 22 May 1988) is a German [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Teutonia Watzenborn-Steinberg]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/regionalliga/rlsw/regionalliga-suedwest-2012/2016-17/teutonia-watzenborn-steinberg-7607/48626/spieler_markus-mueller.html | title = M\u00fcller, Markus | language = German | publisher = kicker.de | accessdate = 10 August 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\nM\u00fcller began his career with [[Erzgebirge Aue]], and made his debut in the [[2. Bundesliga]] in April 2008, replacing [[Florian Heller]] in a 0\u20130 home draw with [[1. FC Kaiserslautern]]. He left Aue in January 2009 to join [[Hallescher FC]] of the [[Regionalliga Nord]], where he spent two and a half seasons, being released in June 2011 after injury had restricted him to just eight appearances in the previous season. He subsequently joined [[SV Babelsberg 03]] of the [[3. Liga]], for whom he scored 12 goals in the [[2011\u201312 3. Liga|2011\u201312 season]]. After Babelsberg were relegated in the 2012\u201313 season, he left to sign for [[Wormatia Worms]], where he spent six months before joining [[Kickers Offenbach]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{fussballdaten|muellermarkus|Markus M\u00fcller}}\n* [http://www.scoresway.com/?sport=soccer&page=person&id=38000 Markus M\u00fcller] at Scoresway\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Muller, Markus}}\n[[Category:1988 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:German footballers]]\n[[Category:FC Erzgebirge Aue players]]\n[[Category:Hallescher FC players]]\n[[Category:SV Babelsberg 03 players]]\n[[Category:Wormatia Worms players]]\n[[Category:Kickers Offenbach players]]\n[[Category:2. Bundesliga players]]\n[[Category:3. Liga players]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n\n\n{{Germany-footy-forward-1980s-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Pelmeen10", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Markus_M%C3%BCller"}
{"title_page": "Virgil Peck Jr.", "text_new": "{{Infobox State Representative\n| name=Virgil Peck Jr.\n| image name=\n| state_house=Kansas\n| state=Kansas\n| district=12th\n| term=January 2005\u2013present\n| preceded=\n| succeeded=Incumbent\n| party=[[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] \n| birth_name=Virgil Peck Jr.\n| birth_date= {{Birth date and age|1959|8|21}}\n| birth_place=\n| death_date=\n| death_place=\n| alma_mater= \n| profession=\n| spouse=\n| residence=Tyro, Kansas\n| religion=\n}}\n'''Virgil Peck Jr.''' (born August 21, 1959) is a [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] member of the [[Kansas House of Representatives]], representing the 12th district (in southeast Kansas, Montgomery County).<ref>http://www.kanfocus.com/FMPro.php?-DB=House_Profiles_KS&-lay=Contact&-format=Contact_House.html&Name=Virgil%20Peck%20Jr.,%20R-12th&-find</ref>  He is the former chairman of the Kansas House Transportation and Public Safety Budget Committees, and the former Republican Majority Caucus Chairman.<ref name=\"peck_will_challenge_2014_11_15_wichita_eagle\">Lowry, Bryan (''Eagle'' Topeka bureau), [http://www.kansas.com/news/politics-government/article3951379.html \"Virgil Peck will challenge Ray Merrick for speaker of Kansas House\"], Nov. 15, 2014, Wichita ''Eagle.''</ref>\n\nPrior to his election, he ran unsuccessfully for House District 11 in 2002, and for [[Kansas Senate]] District 15 in 2000.<ref>[http://votesmart.org/bio.php?can_id=34716 Project Vote Smart - Rep. Virgil Peck ''Biography'']</ref>\n\n==Issue positions==\nPeck identifies as, \"Pro-Low Taxes, Pro-Life, Pro-Education, Pro-Business, Pro-Agriculture,\" and \"Pro-2nd Amendment.\"  He states, \"''We need to address [[property tax]] relief, immigration reform, health care costs, state debt, and bring state government spending under control''.\"<ref>[http://www.virgilpeck.com/ Kansas State Rep. Virgil Peck - Homepage]</ref>\n\n== Controversies==\n\n===Illegal Immigrants' remark===\nOn Monday, March 14, 2011 during an Appropriations Committee discussion about how the State was working to control an increasing feral swine population, Rep. Virgil Peck made a comment about illegal immigrates for which he later issued an apology by stating, \"My statements yesterday were regrettable. Please accept my apology.\"\n\n=== Proposed $10,000 Legislators' Raise===\nIn the 2013 legislative session, Peck introduced a bill to raise lawmakers pay by approximately $10,000 per year. In an effort to garner support for the legislation, and to off-set the salary increase, he put a provision in the bill that would significantly reduce the retirement benefits (KPERS) of lawmakers. The bill failed to get substantial support.<ref name=\"peck_will_challenge_2014_11_15_wichita_eagle\" />\n\n==Committee membership==\nRepresentative Peck serves on the following legislative committees:<ref>{{cite web|title=Representative Virgil Peck|url=http://kslegislature.org/li/b2015_16/members/rep_peck_virgil_1/|website=Kansas State Legislature, 2015-2016 Legislative Sessions|publisher=Kansas Legislative Information System and Services|accessdate=17 July 2016}}</ref>\n* Joint Committee on Legislative Post Audit (Chair)\n* Education Budget\n* Elections\n* Local Government\n* Pensions & Benefits\n\n==Major donors==\nThe top 5 donors to Peck's 2008 campaign were mostly from the insurance industry:<ref>[http://www.followthemoney.org/database/StateGlance/candidate.phtml?c=108120 Follow the Money - 2008 Campaign Contributions]</ref>\n*1. American Home Life Insurance Co\t$1,500 \t\n*2. Farmers Insurance Group \t$1,000 \t\n*3. Jensen International Inc \t$1,000 \t\n*4. Kansas Republican Party \t$1,000\n*5. Kansas Insurance Agents \t$900\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.virgilpeck.com/ Official Website]\n* [http://www.kslegislature.org/legsrv-house/searchHouse.do?rep=4345 Kansas Legislature \u2013 Virgil Peck Jr.]\n* [http://votesmart.org/summary.php?can_id=34716 Project Vote Smart profile]\n* [http://kansasvotes.org/Legislator.aspx?ID=15595 Kansas Votes profile]\n* [http://www.statesurge.com/members/1609-virgil-peck-jr-kansas State Surge - Legislative Profile]\n* Follow the Money campaign contributions:\n** [http://www.followthemoney.org/database/StateGlance/candidate.phtml?c=32295 2000],[http://www.followthemoney.org/database/StateGlance/candidate.phtml?c=18228 2002], [http://www.followthemoney.org/database/StateGlance/candidate.phtml?c=74229 2004], [http://www.followthemoney.org/database/StateGlance/candidate.phtml?c=85253 2006], [http://www.followthemoney.org/database/StateGlance/candidate.phtml?c=108120 2008]\n{{Kansas House of Representatives}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Peck, Virgil Jr.}}\n[[Category:Members of the Kansas House of Representatives]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Kansas Republicans]]\n[[Category:1959 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American politicians]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox State Representative\n| name=Virgil Peck Jr.\n| image name=\n| state_house=Kansas\n| state=Kansas\n| district=12th\n| term=January 2005\u2013present\n| preceded=\n| succeeded=Incumbent\n| party=[[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] \n| birth_name=Virgil Peck Jr.\n| birth_date= {{Birth date and age|1959|8|21}}\n| birth_place=\n| death_date=\n| death_place=\n| alma_mater= \n| profession=\n| spouse=\n| residence=Tyro, Kansas\n| religion=\n}}\n'''Virgil Peck Jr.''' (born August 21, 1959) is a [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] member of the [[Kansas House of Representatives]], representing the 12th district (in southeast Kansas, Montgomery County).<ref>http://www.kanfocus.com/FMPro.php?-DB=House_Profiles_KS&-lay=Contact&-format=Contact_House.html&Name=Virgil%20Peck%20Jr.,%20R-12th&-find</ref>  He is the former chairman of the Kansas House Transportation and Public Safety Budget Committees, and the former Republican Majority Caucus Chairman.<ref name=\"peck_will_challenge_2014_11_15_wichita_eagle\">Lowry, Bryan (''Eagle'' Topeka bureau), [http://www.kansas.com/news/politics-government/article3951379.html \"Virgil Peck will challenge Ray Merrick for speaker of Kansas House\"], Nov. 15, 2014, Wichita ''Eagle.''</ref>\n\nPrior to his election, he ran unsuccessfully for House District 11 in 2002, and for [[Kansas Senate]] District 15 in 2000.<ref>[http://votesmart.org/bio.php?can_id=34716 Project Vote Smart - Rep. Virgil Peck ''Biography'']</ref>\n\n==Issue positions==\nPeck identifies as, \"Pro-Low Taxes, Pro-Life, Pro-Education, Pro-Business, Pro-Agriculture,\" and \"Pro-2nd Amendment.\"  He states, \"''We need to address [[property tax]] relief, immigration reform, health care costs, state debt, and bring state government spending under control''.\"<ref>[http://www.virgilpeck.com/ Kansas State Rep. Virgil Peck - Homepage]</ref>\n\n== Controversies==\n\n===Illegal Immigrants' remark===\nOn Monday, March 14, 2011 during a committee discussion about a state plan to use gunmen in helicopters to control the feral swine population, Rep. Virgil Peck said \"If shooting these immigrating feral hogs works, maybe we have found a (solution) to our illegal immigration problem.\"<ref name=\"peck_will_challenge_2014_11_15_wichita_eagle\" />\nPeck issued an apology by stating, \"My statements yesterday were regrettable. Please accept my apology.\"<ref name=\"peck_will_challenge_2014_11_15_wichita_eagle\" />\n\n=== Proposed $10,000 Legislators' Raise===\nIn the 2013 legislative session, Peck introduced a bill to raise lawmakers pay by $10,000.  The bill failed to get substantial support.<ref name=\"peck_will_challenge_2014_11_15_wichita_eagle\" />\n\n==Committee membership==\nRepresentative Peck serves on the following legislative committees:<ref>{{cite web|title=Representative Virgil Peck|url=http://kslegislature.org/li/b2015_16/members/rep_peck_virgil_1/|website=Kansas State Legislature, 2015-2016 Legislative Sessions|publisher=Kansas Legislative Information System and Services|accessdate=17 July 2016}}</ref>\n* Joint Committee on Legislative Post Audit (Chair)\n* Education Budget\n* Elections\n* Local Government\n* Pensions & Benefits\n\n==Major donors==\nThe top 5 donors to Peck's 2008 campaign were mostly from the insurance industry:<ref>[http://www.followthemoney.org/database/StateGlance/candidate.phtml?c=108120 Follow the Money - 2008 Campaign Contributions]</ref>\n*1. American Home Life Insurance Co\t$1,500 \t\n*2. Farmers Insurance Group \t$1,000 \t\n*3. Jensen International Inc \t$1,000 \t\n*4. Kansas Republican Party \t$1,000\n*5. Kansas Insurance Agents \t$900\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.virgilpeck.com/ Official Website]\n* [http://www.kslegislature.org/legsrv-house/searchHouse.do?rep=4345 Kansas Legislature \u2013 Virgil Peck Jr.]\n* [http://votesmart.org/summary.php?can_id=34716 Project Vote Smart profile]\n* [http://kansasvotes.org/Legislator.aspx?ID=15595 Kansas Votes profile]\n* [http://www.statesurge.com/members/1609-virgil-peck-jr-kansas State Surge - Legislative Profile]\n* Follow the Money campaign contributions:\n** [http://www.followthemoney.org/database/StateGlance/candidate.phtml?c=32295 2000],[http://www.followthemoney.org/database/StateGlance/candidate.phtml?c=18228 2002], [http://www.followthemoney.org/database/StateGlance/candidate.phtml?c=74229 2004], [http://www.followthemoney.org/database/StateGlance/candidate.phtml?c=85253 2006], [http://www.followthemoney.org/database/StateGlance/candidate.phtml?c=108120 2008]\n{{Kansas House of Representatives}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Peck, Virgil Jr.}}\n[[Category:Members of the Kansas House of Representatives]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Kansas Republicans]]\n[[Category:1959 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American politicians]]\n", "name_user": "166.182.80.21", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eProposed $10,000 Legislators' Raise)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Virgil_Peck_Jr."}
{"title_page": "Raghu Kunche", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=June 2019}}\n{{BLP sources|date=May 2012}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name                = Raghu Kunche ( \u0c30\u0c18\u0c41 \u0c15\u0c41\u0c02\u0c1a\u0c47 )\n| image               = Raghukunche.PNG\n| image_size        = 220px\n| caption             = Raghu Kunche\n| background       = solo_singer\n| birth_date          = \n| origin              = Gadarada near [[Rajamahendravaram]], [[East Godavari District|East Godavari]], [[Andhra Pradesh]], [[India]]\n| occupation          = [[Music Director]], Film Producer, [[Playback singer]], [[Lyricist]], [[Actor]], Dubbing artist, Anchor\n| years_active        = 2000\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''Raghu Kunche''' is an Indian film [[music director]], [[playback singer]], actor, [[lyricist]], dubbing artist and anchor in the [[Telugu cinema|Telugu]], [[Tamil cinema|Tamil]] and [[Kannada cinema|Kannada]] film industries, currently residing in [[Hyderabad]], [[Telangana]]. He has won 5 NANDI awards given by the state government of [[Andhra Pradesh]].\n\n==Career==\nRaghu Kunche began his singing career in 2000 with the movie [[Bachi (film)|Bachi]]. He has sung about 600 songs for Telugu Films. Raghu Kunche made his debut as a Music Director for the movie ''[[Bumper Offer]]'' in 2009. He won 5 NANDI Awards in his career. He worked as a Dubbing Artist for movies and anchor for various Telugu TV channels before he became a Playback Singer and then a Music Director.\n\n===Music director===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2009\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Bumper Offer]]''\n| Released 23 October 2009 <br />Nandi Special Jury Award\n|-\n| 2011\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Aha Naa Pellanta (2011 film)|Aha Naa Pellanta]]''\n| Released 2 March 2011\n|-\n| 2011\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Daggaraga Dooramga]]''\n| Released 26 March 2011\n|-\n| 2012\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Devudu Chesina Manushulu (2012 film)|Devudu Chesina Manushulu]]''\n| Released 15 August 2012\n|-\n| 2015\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Ladies & Gentlemen (2015 film)|Ladies & Gentlemen]]''\n| Released 30 January 2015\n|-\n| 2015\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Dongaata (2015 film)|Dongaata]]''\n| Released on 8 May 2015<br />Nominated for Best Music Director at IIFA UTSAVAM\n|-\n| 2015\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Mama Manchu Alludu Kanchu]]''\n| Released on 25 December 2015\n|-\n| 2016\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Viraat]]'' ''(Kannada)''\n| Released on 29 Jan 2016\n|-\n| 2016\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Nayaki]]'' ''(Telugu)''\n| Released on 15 July\n|-\n| 2016\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Nayaki|Nayagi]]'' ''(Tamil)''\n| Released on 16 Sep 2016\n|-\n| 2017\n| scope=\"row\" | ''C/O Godavari (Telugu)''\n\n| 47 DAYS\nUnder Production\n|-\n|}\n\n===Playback singer===\nRaghu Kunche sang about 600 songs in [[Telugu language|Telugu]] films. \"Enduke Ravanamma\" - a song about recession from the movie ''[[Bumper Offer]]'' shot him to fame.\n\nHis most popular songs are:\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|- style=\"background:#cccccc;\"\n! No\n! Song\n! Movie\n! Language\n! Notes\n|-\n| 1\n| Yenduke Ravanamma\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Bumper Offer]]''\n| [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n| Nandi Special Jury Award, Radio mirchi,Big fm,Santhosham Awards\n|-\n| 2\n| Subbalaxmi\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Devudu Chesina Manushulu]]''\n| [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|\n|-\n| 3\n| Raye Raye\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Maryada Ramanna]]''\n| [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|\n|-\n| 4\n| Oh I miss you\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Neninthe]]''\n| [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n| Santhosham Best Singer Award\n|-\n| 5\n| Lachmi Lachmi\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Bachi (film)|Bachi]]''\n| [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|\n|-\n| 6\n| Jai Veeranjaneya\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Idiot (2012 film)|Idiot]]''\n| [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|\n|-\n| 7\n| Golapetti\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Desamuduru]]''\n| [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|\n|-\n| 8\n| Chinukularali\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Aha Naa Pellanta (2011 film)|Aha Naa Pellanta]]''\n| [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|\n|-\n| 9\n| Manasu Manasu mari daggaraga\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Daggaraga Dooramga]]''\n| [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|\n|-\n| 10\n| Vonivesina Deepavali\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Sandakozhi|Pandemkodi]]'' (D)\n| [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|\n|-\n| 11\n| Social Network andi babu\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Ladies & Gentlemen (2015 film)|Ladies and Gentlemen]]''\n| [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|\n|-\n| 12\n| First time ammaayi palakarimputho\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Ladies & Gentlemen (2015 film)|Ladies and Gentlemen]]''\n| [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|\n|-\n| 13\n| Ek do Teen Char\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Anjaan (2014 film)|Sikander]]'' (D)\n| [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|\n|-\n| 14\n| Neelo Gundala\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Jigarthanda (2014 film)|Chikkadu Dorakadu]]'' (D)\n| [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|\n|-\n| 15\n| Yandiro sung by Lakshmi Manchu\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Dongaata (2015 film)|Dongaata]]''\n| [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n| Nominated for Best Music Director IIFA 2015\n|-\n| 16\n| Tingu Tingu Rangadu\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Mama Manchu Alludu Kanchu]]''\n| [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|\n|-\n| 17\n| Gandasu safety pin\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Viraat]]''\n| [[Kannada language|Kannada]]\n|\n|}\n\n===Anchor/Actor/Dubbing Artist===\nRaghu Kunche is actor/anchor/dubbing artist who has acted in many TV serials and played roles in movies and short films.\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\" | TITLE\n! scope=\"col\" | ROLE\n! scope=\"col\" | Notes\n|-\n| Yours lovingly\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Anchor''\n|\n|-\n| Post Box No 1562\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Anchor''\n|\n|-\n| Navaragam\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Anchor''\n|\n|-\n| Antyakshari\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Anchor''\n|\n|-\n| Sanghu Bhala\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Anchor''\n|\n|-\n| Aataina Patina\n!