002/ Biochemist and Nobel Prize winner Stanley Cohen dies in Nashville at age 97]</ref>\n** [[Kirk Douglas]], American actor, director and producer (b. [[1916]])<ref>[https://people.com/movies/kirk-douglas-dead/ Kirk Douglas, Hollywood Icon and Spartacus Star, Dies at 103]</ref>\n* [[February 6]] \u2013 [[Jhon Jairo Vel\u00e1squez]], Colombian hitman and drug dealer (b. [[1962]])<ref>[https://www.cbsnews.com/news/jhon-jairo-velasquez-vasquez-popeye-pablo-escobar-death-today-02-06-2020/ Pablo Escobar's former hitman \"Popeye\" has died at 57] cbsnews.com</ref>\n* [[February 7]]\n** [[Orson Bean]], American actor, comedian and producer (b. [[1928]])<ref>[https://abc7.com/veteran-actor-orson-bean-91-struck-and-killed-by-vehicle-in-venice-friends-say/5912587/ Veteran actor Orson Bean, 91, struck and killed by vehicle in Venice, friends say]</ref>\n** [[Li Wenliang]], Chinese ophthalmologist (b. [[1986]])<ref>[https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinese-doctor-who-issued-early-warning-on-virus-dies-11581019816 Chinese Doctor Who Issued Early Warning on Virus Dies]</ref>\n** [[Nexhmije Pagarusha]], Albanian singer and actress (b. [[1933]])<ref>[https://prishtinainsight.com/albanian-music-icon-nexhmije-pagarusha-dies-at-the-age-of-86/ Albanian music icon Nexhmije Pagarusha dies at the age of 86]</ref>\n* [[February 8]] \u2013 [[Robert Conrad]], American actor (b. [[1935]])<ref>[https://www.tmz.com/2020/02/08/robert-conrad-dead-dies-84-wild-wild-west/ 'Wild Wild West' star Robert Conrad dead at 84]</ref>\n* [[February 9]] \u2013 [[Mirella Freni]], Italian soprano (b. [[1935]])<ref>[https://www.repubblica.it/spettacoli/musica/2020/02/09/news/mirella_freni-248186108/ https://www.repubblica.it/spettacoli/musica/2020/02/09/news/mirella_freni-248186108/] {{in lang|it}}</ref>\n* [[February 11]] \u2013 [[Joseph Shabalala]], South African musician (b. [[1940]])<ref>{{cite news |title=Ladysmith Black Mambazo founder Joseph Shabalala dies |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-51458177 |accessdate=February 11, 2020 |publisher=BBC}}</ref>\n* [[February 12]]\n** [[Christie Blatchford]], Canadian newspaper columnist, journalist and broadcaster (b. [[1951]])<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/canada/article-veteran-journalist-christie-blatchford-was-known-for-her-work-ethic/ |title = Veteran journalist Christie Blatchford was known for her work ethic and wit}}</ref>\n** [[Geert Hofstede]], Dutch social psychologist (b. [[1928]])<ref>[https://geerthofstede.com/geert-hofstede-passed-away-1928-2020-obituary/ Geert Hofstede passed away]</ref>\n* [[February 13]] \u2013 [[Rajendra K. Pachauri]], Indian scientist (b. [[1940]])<ref>[https://indianexpress.com/article/india/ex-teri-chief-r-k-pachauri-dies-at-79-6266916/ Ex-TERI chief R K Pachauri dies at 79]</ref>\n* [[February 14]] \u2013 [[Lynn Cohen]], American actress (b. [[1933]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/lynn-cohen-dead-sex-city-actor-dies-at-86-1279546|title=Lynn Cohen, 'Sex and the City' Actor, Dies at 86|website=The Hollywood Reporter |accessdate=February 15, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[February 15]] \u2013 [[Caroline Flack]], English presenter (b. [[1979]])<ref>[https://metro.co.uk/2020/02/15/caroline-flack-dead-aged-40-love-island-tv-presenter-dies-12246583/ Love Island presenter Caroline Flack dies aged 40]</ref>\n* [[February 16]]\n** [[Zoe Caldwell]], Australian actress (b. [[1933]])<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2020/feb/19/zoe-caldwell-obituary/ Zoe Caldwell obituary, leading classical stage actor and four-times Tony award winner, whose career spanned three continents]</ref>\n** [[Harry Gregg]], Northern Irish footballer (b. [[1932]])<ref>[https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2020/02/17/harry-gregg-former-manchester-united-goalkeeper-munich-air-disaster/ Harry Gregg, former Manchester United goalkeeper and Munich air disaster hero, dies aged 87]</ref>\n** [[Larry Tesler]], American computer scientist (b. [[1945]])<ref>{{cite web|title=Lawr