th-2020/home/en/|title=International Year of Plant Health 2020|last=|first=|date=|website=Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=January 18, 2020}}</ref> 2020 has been designated as '''International Year of Sound''' by the [[International Commission for Acoustics]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sound2020.org/|title=2020 - International Year of Sound|publisher=[[International Commission for Acoustics]]|language=en|access-date=February 15, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] has led to severe global [[Socio-economic impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|socioeconomic disruption]].<ref name=\"NYT-20200229\">{{cite news |work=[[The New York Times]] |title=Here Comes the Coronavirus Pandemic: Now, after many fire drills, the world may be facing a real fire |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/29/opinion/sunday/corona-virus-usa.html |date=February 29, 2020 |access-date=March 1, 2020 |department=Editorial}}</ref>\n<!-- {{Skip to top and bottom}}\n{{sts|January}} -->\n\n==Events==\n===January===\n* [[January 2]] \u2013 The [[government of New South Wales]], [[Australia]], declares a [[state of emergency]] whilst the [[government of Victoria]], Australia declares a state of disaster amid large [[2019\u201320 Australian bushfire season|bushfires]] that have killed as many as 500 million animals.<ref>{{cite news |title='Going to be a blast furnace': State of emergency again for NSW |url=https://www.smh.com.au/national/nsw/going-to-be-a-blast-furnace-state-of-emergency-again-for-nsw-20200102-p53ofd.html |accessdate=January 3, 2020 |work=The Sydney Morning Herald |date=January 2, 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Victorian fires: state of disaster declared as evacuation ordered and 28 people missing |url=https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2020/jan/03/victoria-fires-state-of-disaster-declared-as-evacuation-ordered-and-second-man-found-dead |acce