hore|Aegis Ashore]] missile defense system in [[Poland]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usnews.com/news/world/articles/2018-03-22/poland-says-us-missile-shield-site-delayed-until-2020|title=Poland Says U.S. Missile Shield Site Delayed Until 2020|website=usnews.com|accessdate=June 29, 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Liberia]] will become the first nation of the world to completely stop cutting down its trees in return for development aid \u2013 [[Norway]] will pay the impoverished country $150 million to stop [[deforestation]] by 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-29321143|title=Liberia signs 'transformational' deal to stem deforestation|date=September 23, 2014|work=BBC|accessdate=September 23, 2014}}</ref>\n* The [[Grand Egyptian Museum]], described as the largest archaeological museum in the world, is expected to be completed.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.osiristours.com/the-highly-anticipated-grand-egyptian-museum-will-finally-open-its-doors-in-2020//|title=The Highly Anticipated Grand Egyptian Museum Will Finally Open Its Doors in 2020|language=en-US|access-date=November 26, 2019|date=April 10, 2019}}</ref>\n* The [[New Administrative Capital]] of Egypt is expected to be completed.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://english.ahram.org.eg/NewsContent/1/64/322162/Egypt/Politics-/,-state-employees-to-be-reassigned-to-Egypts-New-A.aspx/|title=50,000 state employees to be reassigned to Egypt's New Administrative Capital in 2020: Ministry|language=en-US|access-date=November 26, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Deaths ==\n{{Further|:Category:2020 deaths}}\n\n===January===\n{{Main|Deaths in January 2020}}\n[[File:Qasem Soleimani with Zolfaghar Order (cropped).jpg|thumb|120px|[[Qasem Soleimani]]]]\n[[File:NeilPeart (cropped).JPG|thumb|120px|[[Neil Peart]]]]\n[[File:Buck Henry (4970849739).jpg|thumb|120px|[[Buck Henry]]]]\n[[File:Omani_Qaboos_bin_Said_Al_Said_(cropped).jpg|thumb|120px|[[Qaboos bin Said]]]]\n[[File:Terry Jones Monty Python O2 Arena (cropped).jpg|thumb|120