 London\n| isbn      = 0-85591-000-3\n| ref       = harv\n}}\n*{{cite journal |last=Tanner |first=Jim |title=The First Day of Third Ypres: the 1st Battalion the Prince of Wales's (North Staffordshire) Regiment |journal=Stand To! The Journal of the Western Front Association |volume=109 |year=2017 |pages=45\u201351 |ref=harv }}\n* {{cite book\n| title     = War Diary 2nd Battalion North Staffordshire Regiment. 29 August 1915 to 9 December 1915\n| year      = 1915\n| publisher = War Office\n| ref       = {{harvid|War Diary|1915}}\n}}\n*{{cite book\n| last      = Westlake\n| first     = Ray\n| title     = Tracing the Rifle Volunteers\n| location  = Barnsley\n| publisher = Pen and Sword\n| year      = 2010\n| isbn      = 978-1-84884-211-3\n| ref       = harv\n}}\n*{{cite web\n |last=Young \n |first=A. \n |url=http://british-army-units1945on.co.uk/territorial-army-royal-artillery/564-591-regiments.html \n |title=British Army units from 1945 on; Royal Artillery, Territorial Army 1947\u201367 \n |ref=harv \n |url-status=dead \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160110025402/http://british-army-units1945on.co.uk/territorial-army-royal-artillery/564-591-regiments.html \n |archivedate=10 January 2016 \n}}\n\n{{Mercian Regiment}}\n{{British Infantry Regiments World War I}}\n\n{{good article}}\n\n[[Category:Infantry regiments of the British Army]]\n[[Category:Military units and formations in Staffordshire]]\n[[Category:Military units and formations established in 1881]]\n[[Category:Regiments of the British Army in World War I]]\n[[Category:Regiments of the British Army in World War II]]\n[[Category:Military units and formations disestablished in 1959]]\n[[Category:1881 establishments in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Military units and formations in Burma in World War II|R]]\n", "name_user": "GrindtXX", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eAmalgamation:italics", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_Staffordshire_Regiment"}
